Art;<br><br>
One thing we need to learn is that it’s all right to color outside the line. <br><br>
M24 uses big crayons, so he does it by accident. <br><br>
I like sweeping broad strokes with plenty of water so that the colors run into each other so that you can no longer see the lines. <br><br>
SW uses color pencils but keeps getting saliva all over the screen. <br><br>
Chet just wants to make sure we all have equal amount of paper and crayons.<br><br>
Tom wants us to remember that Tennessee is prettier then Nam.<br><br>
Art, you seem to throw a lot of pretty flowers into all your pictures and I like that. <br>
But we all need to color outside the line more often, if nothing else, just because it feels good.<br><br>
In War and Peace<br><br>
Cookie<br><br>

